{
  "power_respect_guidance_summary": "As the teacher, Keating uses his higher power to provide a firm yet mentoring correction to his student. The neutral respect level maintains a professional and instructional tone, using 'Charles' to signal a serious pedagogical moment while emphasizing the student's accountability.",
  "translation_power_respect_only": "汲取生命的精华并不代表要被骨头噎住，查尔斯。你对自己和那些关心你的人依然负有责任。"
}

{
  "power_respect_guidance_summary": "The speaker is a student addressing his teacher, who holds higher institutional authority. The respect level is neutral, reflecting a candid and direct manner of questioning that lacks formal deference but remains within the bounds of a student-teacher dialogue. The tone should convey confusion and a slight sense of protest.",
  "translation_power_respect_only": "但我以为——"
